      "text": "Mam ochotę grać w tenisa. Mam ochotę means I feel like. Grać means to play. W tenisa means tennis — notice that tenisa is in the accusative case after w when talking about playing a sport. So: I feel like playing tennis. Polish speakers use mam ochotę constantly when suggesting activities. It sounds warmer and more natural than chcę in social situations. Say it: I feel like playing tennis."
